shared_text:
Tawnie Anger is with Ashley Scorse.
May 21 at 7:54 PM Â·

It was such a fun day today as we started this morning by honoring and saying goodbye to our 7th graders and then this evening by honoring and promoting our 8th graders. It was so fun to see the kids with their cars all decorated and to get to show them how much we love them. We really got robbed this last quarter as we didnâ€™t get to finish the year with our kids and it was just so nice to get to see them again, even if it was just for a few minutes.ðŸ’™ðŸ’› I am also glad that I got to spend the majority of the day with my co-workers. I am truly blessed to work at Pima Junior High with all of these amazing staff and students.

In order to be compliant with the Governor's Executive Orders and the laws requiring monthly public school board meetings, the Pima School Board April meeting will be broadcast on a YouTube channel. https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCtqek3vGc5tQInRVc_2nvcA

The meeting will begin at 6:00pm tomorrow Thursday, April 16.

The agenda for the meeting can be accessed at https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_342436/site_342437/Documents/April-16-2020-Agenda.pdf

Members of the public who do not have access to YouTube can call-in to hear the meeting at 561-614-1184â€¬ the PIN is 951 782 910 all callers will need to be muted.

Individuals wishing to share comments or concerns with the board should sent an email to srickert@pimaschools.com. All comments received before the meeting will be read at the "Call to the Public" agenda item.

Thank you for your continued support for Pima Schools.

Sincerely,
Mr. Sean Rickert
Superintendent
(928)387-8002

shared_text:
Tawnie Anger
March 28 at 10:47 AM Â·

Always remember: YOU'RE DOING THE WORK!

.. If you tried to reach a parent all week, and haven't heard back, you're doing the work.

.. If you spent 5 hours trying to broadcast your support sessions live, and still haven't figured it out, you're doing the work.

.. If you attempted to help 50 students, and only 3 logged on, you're doing the work.

.. If you emailed students and offered help, and none of them responded, you're doing the work.

.. If you spent all day learning a new online platform, and you realized it's no good, you're doing the work.

.. If you are concerned about getting students connected to learning, you're doing the work.

Focus on what you ATTEMPTED, ACCOMPLISHED and LEARNED this week. Most of the kids have not connected with a full lesson this week, but I know they are learning so much. The most important lesson they learned is how much their school community cares about them.

I am grateful in the midst of this abnormality, I work with such a dedicated group of educators.

UPDATE:NEW TIMES - MEALS WILL BE AVAILABLE
Beginning Monday, March 23.

From 8:30am to Noon Breakfast and Lunch can be picked up (one trip both meals).

Must have child under 18 with you to get meal (one day's meals for each child present). Any child under 18 is eligible to receive meals (no FRL app or PUSD enrollment required).

A table will be set up in front of the Pima Cafeteria on Main Street. Only one person needs to get out of the car. Meals will be made to go for offsite consumption (the cafeteria will not be open). We ask folks to be patient and not form a crowd at the cafeteria.

Menu info will be made available when we have it..

Update:

At this time we still have not received any positive test results for any students or employees. The instance involving the staff member who was tested Wednesday evening is the only case where we are awaiting test results. We have been in contact with the Graham County Health Department and expect test results to be delivered Friday, March 13 by 6:00 pm.

Once we have more information we will do our best to communicate with all those affected. Thank you for your patience as we work through this process.

post_text:
School Closed Thursday, March 12, 2020

As you know the nation is being gripped by the spread of the coronavirus. We have received a report of possible exposure to an unknown illness for some students at Pima Elementary School. Parents of those students have received separate notification. Out of an abundance of caution, while the County health department determines if this is in fact an incidence of coronavirus, Pima Schools will be closed for Thursday, March 12.

Information about extracurricular activities will come in subsequent notifications.

Many members of the Pima Spiritline Squad participated in the Dance if Off! A Dance Competition event at the David M. Player CFA on January 26.
The Team took 1st place in Senior Production!
Kylie and Kiora Wood placed 1st in Duets!
Gabby Thompson, Kiora Wood and Ashley Velasquez placed 2nd in the Trio Category!
Ashley Velasquez also placed 3rd in the Solo Category!
and Kiora Wood, Kylie Wood, Marissa Launer and Ashley Velasquez placed 3rd in the Small Group Category!

These girls id an amazing job of representing PHS Spirit through their excellent sportsmanship, hard work and positive attitude!

Home - Pima Unified School District

Arizona Rural Schools Association
February 27, 2018 at 2:00 PM Â·

#MeetOurMembers: Pima Unified School District

Pima Unified School District is located in the historical Town of Pima, Arizona, and they serve the communities of Pima, Bryce, and Eden in southeastern Arizona. Their district includes one high school (grades 9â€“12), one junior high (grades 7â€“8) and one elementary school (grades Kâ€“6) with a district student population of approximately 690 students. They pride themselves on their personalized instruction, their focus on individual needs and learning styles, and their small class sizes.

We are so lucky to have Pima Unified School District as a part of #ARSA! To find out more about this amazing school district, please visit their website >> https://www.pimaschools.org
